HEADWORD: Carbonometer
<hw>Car`bon*om"e*ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Carbon</ets> + <ets>-meter</ets>.]</ety> <def>An instrument
for detecting and measuring the amount of carbon which is present, or
more esp. the amount of carbon dioxide, by its action on limewater or by
other means.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>carbonous</ent>⟦br⟧
